---
// Four honest figures in a hairline grid. The HTML ships the final values;
// the motion layer replays them as count-ups (the third one counts down —
// saccades per line going to zero is the whole product).
---

<section id="numbers" class="nums section">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="sec-head" data-reveal>
      <p class="sec-label">The numbers</p>
      <h2 class="sec-h2">Honest arithmetic.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="num" data-reveal>
        <b class="v" data-count="238">238</b>
        <span class="l">wpm — the average adult reader<sup>*</sup></span>
      </div>
      <div class="num" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.06">
        <b class="v" data-count="700">700</b>
        <span class="l">wpm — the demo at the top of this page</span>
      </div>
      <div class="num" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.12">
        <b class="v" data-count="0" data-count-from="8">0</b>
        <span class="l">eye movements per line, down from ~8</span>
      </div>
      <div class="num" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="0.18">
        <b class="v" data-count="8">8</b>
        <span class="l">ways to get text in, from paste to cloud link</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="note" data-reveal>
      No skipped words, no skimming tricks — every word is shown, just without the round trip
      your eyes make at the end of each line. 2–3× is what practiced RSVP readers comfortably
      hold with full comprehension.
      <span class="src"><sup>*</sup>Brysbaert (2019), meta-analysis of 190 reading studies.</span>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sec-head { margin-bottom: clamp(32px, 5vh, 48px); }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--line);
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
  }
  .num {
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: clamp(22px, 3vw, 34px) clamp(18px, 2.4vw, 28px);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    transition: background var(--t-flick) var(--ease);
  }
  .v {
    font-size: clamp(38px, 5.4vw, 64px);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .l {
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .l sup { color: var(--accent); }

  .note {
    margin: 26px 0 0;
    color: var(--dim);
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 72ch;
  }
  .note .src { display: block; margin-top: 6px; font-size: 11px; }
  .note sup { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    .grid { grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr); }
  }
</style>
